                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.816,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion this morning in case 13-1034 Mellouli v. Lynch."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.816,
                        "stop": 284.28,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.816,
                                "stop": 30.348,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In this case we answer the question how should immigration judges apply a deportation provision defined with reference to Federal drug laws to an alien convicted of drug paraphernalia possession, an offense under State Law but not Federal Law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.348,
                                "stop": 41.243,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Petitioner Moones Mellouli, a lawful permanent resident, pleaded guilty to possessing drug paraphernalia in violation of Kansas law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.243,
                                "stop": 50.893,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The paraphernalia Mellouli was charged with possessing: one sock in which he had placed four orange tablets."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.893,
                                "stop": 65.681,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The criminal charge and plea agreement cannot identify the substance concealed in the sock but Mellouli had acknowledged prior to the charge and plea that the tablets were Adderall."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.681,
                                "stop": 70.475,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Mellouli received the suspended sentence and a used probation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.475,
                                "stop": 82.015,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "After he successfully completed probation an immigration Judge ordered him deported based on the Kansas drug paraphernalia possession conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.015,
                                "stop": 92.577,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Board of Immigration Appeals (BIA) affirmed the order and the Eighth Circuit denied Mellouli\u0027s petition for review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.577,
                                "stop": 95.844,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We now reverse the Eighth Circuit\u0027s judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.844,
                                "stop": 119.598,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Mellouli was deported under a provision of Federal Immigration Law that authorizes deportation of an alien convicted of a violation of any law or regulation of a state, the United States, or a foreign country relating to a controlled substance as defined in Section 802 of Title 21."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.598,
                                "stop": 130.419,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Section 802 limits the term controlled substance to a drug or other substance includied in one of five federal schedules to determine"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.419,
                                "stop": 145.283,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "whether an alien is deportable under this provision we apply an approach called categorical, under that approach we looked at the statutory definition of the alien\u0027s offense of conviction not to the particulars of the alien\u0027s conduct."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.283,
                                "stop": 152.41,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The drug paraphernalia law under which Mellouli was convicted by definition does relate to a controlled substance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.41,
                                "stop": 160.671,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Kansas statute makes it unlawful to use or possess any drug paraphernalia to store or conceal a controlled substance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.671,
                                "stop": 169.031,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But does the Kansas law relate to a controlled substance as defined in 21 USC Section 802."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.031,
                                "stop": 170.941,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our answer is no."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.941,
                                "stop": 183.653,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The word \u201ccontrolled substance\u0022 in the Kansas statute refers to substances controlled under Kansas\u0027 own schedule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.653,
                                "stop": 189.386,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is immaterial under the State Law whether a substance is defined in Section 802."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.386,
                                "stop": 197.148,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "At the time of Mellouli\u0027s conviction Kansas\u0027 schedule included at least nine substances not included in the Federal list."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 197.148,
                                "stop": 209.087,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Nothing in the record of Mellouli\u0027s conviction shows that a drug on an 802 schedule figured as an element of the crime for which he was charged and convicted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 209.087,
                                "stop": 219.037,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The government contends that aliens who commit drug crimes and states whose schedules substantially overlap the Federal schedules are deportable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 219.037,
                                "stop": 232.616,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "States statute that criminalize hundreds of federally controlled drugs and a handful of similar substances on state but not federal list, the government urges, all laws relating to federally controlled substances."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 232.616,
                                "stop": 244.079,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But the BIA has their own deportation statute to require a direct link between an alien\u0027s crime of conviction and a particular federally controlled drug."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 244.079,
                                "stop": 246.643,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That link is missing here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.643,
                                "stop": 258.372,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Construction of the statute must be faithful to its text which limits the meaning of controlled substance for deportation purposes to the substances controlled under Section 802."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 258.372,
                                "stop": 270.356,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Decretive deportation we therefore hold the government must connect an element of the aliens conviction to a drug defined in Section 802."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 270.356,
                                "stop": 277.286,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The government did not do so here, accordingly Mellouli\u0027s deportation order cannot stand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 277.286,
                                "stop": 284.28,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Alito joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
